{
  "text": "Jim has a personal question which is about to be published. He asks, it seems that my balancing work has shifted from more peripheral concerns such as patience slash impatience to learning, to open myself in unconditional love, to accepting myself as whole and perfect, and then to accepting myself as the creator. If this is a normal progression of focus for balancing, wouldn't it be more efficient once this is discovered for a person to work on the acceptance of self as creator rather than work peripherally on the secondary and tertiary results of not accepting the self. The term efficiency has misleading connotations in the context of doing work in the disciplines of the personality, in order to be of more full efficiency in the central acceptance of the self. It is first quite necessary to know the distortions of the self, which the entity is accepting each thought and action needs must then be scrutinized for the precise foundation of the distortions of any reactions. Shall lead to the more central task of acceptance. However, the architrave must be in place before the structure is builded.",
